That explains it: on the success screen you likely use the message key directly:

```html
<h1 th:utext="#{salesPoints.heading}">
```

So Thymeleaf reads the property and renders `<br>` as HTML.

On the error screen, your value comes from the controller as a model attribute:

```html
<h1 th:utext="${title}">
```

If it still shows `<br>`, the most likely reason is that the controller is adding an **escaped** value, like `Oups, un problème&lt;br&gt;technique...`, or the property file contains escaped text.

Best fix: don’t resolve the title in the controller. Pass the **message key** to the template, then let Thymeleaf resolve it with `#{...}` like the success screen.

## Controller

Change from:

```java
mv.addObject("title", messageSource.getMessage("error.technical.title", null, locale));
```

to:

```java
mv.addObject("titleKey", "error.technical.title");
```

For example:

```java
@GetMapping("/error/technical")
public ModelAndView technicalError() {
    ModelAndView mv = new ModelAndView("views/ui-error");
    mv.addObject("pageTitleKey", "error.technical.pageTitle");
    mv.addObject("iconPath", "/images/icons/tools.svg");
    mv.addObject("titleKey", "error.technical.title");
    mv.addObject("messageKey", "error.technical.message");
    mv.addObject("strongMessageKey", "error.technical.strongMessage");
    return mv;
}
```

And:

```java
@GetMapping("/error/no-sales-point")
public ModelAndView noSalesPoint() {
    ModelAndView mv = new ModelAndView("views/ui-error");
    mv.addObject("pageTitleKey", "error.noSalesPoint.pageTitle");
    mv.addObject("iconPath", "/images/icons/warning.svg");
    mv.addObject("titleKey", "error.noSalesPoint.title");
    mv.addObject("messageKey", "error.noSalesPoint.message");
    mv.addObject("strongMessageKey", "error.noSalesPoint.strongMessage");
    return mv;
}
```

## Template

Use dynamic message lookup:

```html
<title th:text="#{${pageTitleKey}}">Erreur</title>

<h1 th:utext="#{${titleKey}}">
    Oups, un problème<br>technique est survenu.
</h1>

<p class="message" th:text="#{${messageKey}}">
    Nous n’avons pas pu charger les données nécessaires.
</p>

<p class="strong-message" th:text="#{${strongMessageKey}}">
    Réessayez dans quelques minutes.
</p>
```

## Properties

```properties
error.technical.title=Oups, un problème<br>technique est survenu.
error.noSalesPoint.title=Oups, votre point de vente<br>n’est pas encore défini.
```

This makes the error screen behave the same as the success screen: translation comes through `#{...}`, and `th:utext` renders the `<br>`.
